## Implementation Plan

### Problem
During `sentry setup`, when an unsupported shell (e.g. xonsh, nushell) is
detected, completions are skipped entirely. Most systems have bash installed,
and many custom shells can use bash completions as a compatibility layer.

### Solution
1. Add `isBashAvailable()` to `src/lib/shell.ts` using `Bun.which("bash")`.
2. Extract `tryBashCompletionFallback()` in setup.ts to keep cognitive
   complexity within the lint limit.
3. When `handleCompletions()` encounters an unsupported (non-sh/ash) shell:
   - If bash is found → install bash completions and tell the user
   - If bash is not found → fall back to the existing "Not supported" message

### User-visible output (e.g. xonsh with bash present)
    Completions: Your shell (unknown) is not directly supported
          Installed bash completions as a fallback: ~/.local/share/bash-completion/completions/sentry

### Files changed
- src/lib/shell.ts          — isBashAvailable()
- src/commands/cli/setup.ts — tryBashCompletionFallback(), handleCompletions()
- test/commands/cli/setup.test.ts — two new tests, one updated
- test/lib/shell.test.ts    — isBashAvailable test
